fuzz_extract_mem: assert `ctx->filter_offset == filter_length` at
dmc_unrar.c:8014 inside dmc_unrar_rar50_decompress. After the
decompressor is asked to fill filter_length bytes into filter memory
(dmc_unrar_rar50_decompress_block call at line 8008), it returns
DMC_UNRAR_OK without having written the full expected byte count,
leaving filter_offset < filter_length. A malformed RAR5 stream can
terminate or run dry while a filter slot is still waiting for input.
161-byte minimized input, surfaced on the 10-minute post-Phase-6
fuzz_extract_mem run. Fixed by turning the ASSERT at 8014 into a
runtime check that returns DMC_UNRAR_INVALID_DATA on a short fill;
the symmetric rar30 path at dmc_unrar.c:7170 got the same guard.
